BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:From Idea to Impact: Publishing Your Work — Open Access Publishi
 ng: Mandates\, Policies\, Support
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260423T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260423T210000
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52332244113501
DESCRIPTION:Maximize your research impact and global reach by publishing O
 pen Access. In this workshop we will show you how to use UC’s transforma
 tive agreements and other library initiatives to have the Library cover yo
 ur publishing fees\, ensuring your work is freely available from day one. 
 We will briefly address staying compliant with federal public access manda
 tes\, and provide a short overview of the UC Open Access Policies.\n \n\nN
 o previous experience is required. All disciplines are welcome. \n\nPlease
  register for the Zoom link.\n\nThis six-workshop series is a collaboratio
 n between the library's Scholarly Communications Program\, the Researcher 
 Services department\, and Blaisdell Medical Library. For any questions\, p
 lease contact the Scholarly Communication Officer Michael Ladisch (mladisc
 h@ucdavis.edu). Check our events calendar for more publishing workshops.
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/open-access-publishing
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Emerging Topics: Pop-Up Talk
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260424T210000
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51843766520718
DESCRIPTION:DataLab's pop-up talks are by DataLab faculty\, staff\, and af
 filiates and focus on emerging topics\, tips\, and trends in data science.
  Join us for the Winter 2026 series on alternating Fridays from 1-2 PM at 
 DataLab. After the talk stick around for refreshments during our weekly so
 cial "Data Science Cafe" from 2-3 PM.\n\n \n\nThis event is offered in per
 son. All members of the University of California system are welcome to att
 end. Advance registration requested but not required!\n\n \n\nCan’t atte
 nd this event? Materials from prior UC Davis DataLab workshops are availab
 le on DataLab's website. Check out our workshop schedule for other upcomin
 g trainings. Questions? Email datalab-training@ucdavis.edu. \n\n \n\nQuest
 ions? Contact datalab-training@ucdavis.edu.
LOCATION:Shields Library\, 360
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/pop-up-talk-w2026-0426
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
